<BaseLayout title="About">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <div class="inline-block relative group max-w-36 md:max-w-48 transition-all duration-300 rotate-3 hover:rotate-0 float-right ml-4 md:ml-8 mb-4 md:mb-8 -top-10"><img src="/image/andrew.png" alt="Grayscale and dithered picture of Andrew" class="rounded-md block group-hover:ring-4 group-hover:ring-blue-500 transition-all duration-300" /></div>
  <p>I’m a Principal Engineer at <a href="https://www.mitre.org">MITRE</a>, where I lead the development of <a href="https://github.com/mitre/hipcheck">Hipcheck</a>, a tool to empower open-source maintainers and users to assess the supply-chain risk of their dependencies.</p>
  <p>I also serve as a member of the <a href="https://omnibor.io">OmniBOR Core Team</a>, including leading creation of the <a href="https://github.com/omnibor/omnibor-rs">Rust library and <code>omnibor</code> CLI</a>.</p>
  <h2 id="where-to-find-me">Where to Find Me</h2>
  <p><a href="https://github.com/alilleybrinker">GitHub</a> · <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/alilleybrinker.com">Bluesky</a> · <a href="https://hachyderm.io/@alilleybrinker">Mastodon</a> · <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/alilleybrinker">LinkedIn</a> · <a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/user?id=alilleybrinker">Hacker News</a> · <a href="https://lobste.rs/~alilleybrinker">Lobste.rs</a> · <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/alilleybrinker/">Reddit</a></p>
  <h3>Getting in Touch</h3><p>I don't check every platform equally often. If you want to get in touch, the best way is to direct message me on <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/alilleybrinker.com">Bluesky</a>. If you want to chat securely, ask me for my Signal username.</p>
  <h2 id="ai-policy">AI Policy</h2><p>The words on this site were written by a human (Andrew) with care. If AI content is ever posted to this site, it will always be made clear what content is AI-generated.</p>
  <h2 id="my-name">My Name</h2><p>“Lilley Brinker” is my full last name. Two parts, no hyphen. When my wife and I got married we combined our last names without a hyphen. My last name is not “Brinker” and it is not correct to call me “Mr. Brinker”.</p><p>“Lilley” is pronounced like the word “lily”.</p>
  <h2>Previous Things</h2><p>Served as Technical Editor for a <a href="https://www.manning.com/books/write-powerful-rust-macros">book on Rust procedural macros</a> · Earned a Master of Computer Science degree from <a href="https://csweb.rice.edu/">Rice University</a> · Maintained a <a href="https://github.com/alilleybrinker/langs-in-rust">list of programming languages written in Rust</a> · and more.</p>
